
2. Dashboard Architecture (5 Executive Views)
A. CIO / Executive Cockpit (Strategic View)

Purpose: Business health & risk

Key Metrics

Overall customer sentiment trend (WoW, MoM)

First Call Resolution (FCR)

Repeat call rate

Escalation rate

Compliance risk score

Training effectiveness index

Cost per resolution

Agent productivity vs satisfaction correlation

Visuals

Heatmaps by product / region

Trend lines with anomaly alerts

Top 5 systemic issues driving calls

Voice of Customer (VoC) word cloud

Value to CIO

Links customer pain → operational root cause

Enables investment decisions (training vs process vs tech)

B. Customer Experience (CX) Dashboard

Purpose: Improve service quality

Metrics

Average sentiment by call stage (start → end)

Sentiment recovery rate (bad start → good end)

Hold-time impact on sentiment

Top negative triggers (billing, login, delays, outages)

Churn-risk language detection

Advanced Insights

Calls where sentiment drops sharply (journey breaks)

Phrases that calm customers vs escalate them

Channel leakage (calls that should not have been calls)

Value

Improves scripts

Redesigns IVR & self-service

Feeds product/process fixes

C. Agent Performance & Coaching Dashboard

Purpose: Fair, objective agent evaluation

Agent Scorecard (Composite Index)

Communication clarity score

Empathy score

Compliance adherence

Talk-to-listen ratio

Interruption frequency

Resolution success

Sentiment delta (customer mood improvement)

Peer Benchmarking

Agent vs team vs top quartile

Skill-based strengths/weaknesses

Improvement trajectory over time

Drill-down

Play call snippets for coaching

Highlight “gold standard” calls

Flag burnout or stress patterns

Important:
This is not punitive — framed as coaching intelligence.

D. Training & L&D Intelligence Dashboard

Purpose: Build smarter training programs

Insights

Skill gaps by cohort (new hires vs tenured)

Which training modules improve which metrics

Before-after sentiment and resolution comparison

Knowledge gaps by product or policy

Outputs

Personalized training recommendations per agent

Micro-learning topics auto-generated from real calls

Library of “best response examples”

Value

Training ROI becomes measurable

Continuous learning loop from real data

E. Risk, Compliance & Quality Assurance Dashboard

Purpose: Prevent regulatory and reputational damage

Capabilities

Mandatory disclosure detection

Prohibited phrase alerts

Missed compliance steps

Aggressive language detection

Vulnerable customer indicators

Alerts

High-risk calls flagged in near real-time

Agent-level risk accumulation score

Policy drift detection over time

Value

Reduces audit cost

Protects brand

Enables proactive remediation

3. Advanced & “Other Stuff” (High-Value Add-Ons)
1. Predictive Intelligence

Predict call escalation likelihood

Predict repeat caller probability

Identify customers at churn risk

Forecast call volume by issue type

2. Process Improvement Engine

Map calls to broken processes

Identify policies causing friction

Quantify cost of poor processes

3. Product Feedback Loop

Extract product bugs & feature requests

Rank by frequency + sentiment severity

Feed directly to product teams

4. Agent Well-Being & Burnout Monitor

Rising stress language patterns

Increasing interruption behavior

Declining empathy over time

This protects both employees and service quality.

5. AI-Assisted Supervisor Tools

Auto-generated call summaries

Suggested coaching notes

Recommended script improvements

“What top agents say differently” insights

4. Governance & Trust (Critical)

As CIO, you’ll care about this.

Explainable AI scores (no black boxes)

Bias monitoring (accent, gender, region)

Human-in-the-loop reviews

Clear separation of coaching vs disciplinary use

Data retention & privacy controls

5. Success Metrics (How We Prove Value)

Within 6–9 months:

↑ FCR by 10–15%

↓ repeat calls by 12–20%

↓ average handle time (without hurting sentiment)

↑ agent engagement & retention

↓ compliance incidents

Measurable training ROI
